President Biden has declared a major disaster in South Dakota due to flooding that occurred from April 9 to May 5, 2023. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, as well as the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. The affected areas include various counties and the Sisseton-Wahpeton Oyate of the Lake Traverse Reservation. Hazard mitigation measures will also receive federal funding. Kenneth G. Clark of FEMA has been appointed to coordinate federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.